          <div class='page-header'>
            <h1 class='name'>
              <span class='type'>class</span>
              Patterns::Command
            </h1>
          </div>
          <section id='content'>
            <div id='text'>
              <div id='description'>

                <p><a href="Command.html">Command</a> -&gt; <a
                href="../Object.html">Object</a></p>

                <p>Base Class that acts as a receiver and allows execution for a command while
                also storing status and description</p>

                <p>From Design Patterns (Gang of Four)</p>

                <pre>-  Command  declares an interface for executing an operation.</pre>
              </div>
              <div id='context'>
              </div>
              <div id='section'>
                <div id='attribute-list'>
                  <h2 class='section-bar'>Attributes</h2>
                  <div class='name-list'>
                    <table>
                      <tr class='top-aligned-row context-row'>
                        <td class='context-item-name'>
                          <a name='attribute-i-description'>description</a>
                        </td>
                        <td class='context-item-value'>[RW]</td>
                        <td class='context-item-desc'>
                          <ul><li><ul><li>
                          <p>+@description+ - stores the description that is passed to the initializer
                          upon object instantiation n * - +@status+ - the most recent status of the
                          command</p>
                          </li></ul>
                          </li></ul>
                        </td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr class='top-aligned-row context-row'>
                        <td class='context-item-name'>
                          <a name='attribute-i-status'>status</a>
                        </td>
                        <td class='context-item-value'>[RW]</td>
                        <td class='context-item-desc'>
                          <ul><li><ul><li>
                          <p>+@description+ - stores the description that is passed to the initializer
                          upon object instantiation n * - +@status+ - the most recent status of the
                          command</p>
                          </li></ul>
                          </li></ul>
                        </td>
                      </tr>
                    </table>

                    <a name='method-c-new'></a>
                    <section class='method public-class' id='method-method-c-new'>
                      <h3 class='synopsis'>
                        <span class='name'>new</span>
                        <span class='arguments'>(description)</span>
                      </h3>
                      <div class='description'>

                        <p>Initializes the <a href="Command.html">Command</a> Class Designed to be
                        called by a child class in its initialize method</p>
                        <ul><li>
                        <p><code>description</code> - The description of the sub class</p>
                        </li></ul>

                        <p>Examples</p>

                        <pre class="ruby">=<span class="ruby-operator">&gt;</span> <span class="ruby-comment">#inside child class</span>&#x000A;=<span class="ruby-operator">&gt;</span> <span class="ruby-keyword">def</span> <span class="ruby-identifier">initialize</span>&#x000A;=<span class="ruby-operator">&gt;</span>  <span class="ruby-identifier">desc</span> = <span class="ruby-string">&#39;A new child class of Command&#39;</span>&#x000A;=<span class="ruby-operator">&gt;</span>  <span class="ruby-keyword">super</span>(<span class="ruby-identifier">desc</span>) <span class="ruby-comment"># (calls the super class&#39; initialize function defined below)</span>&#x000A;=<span class="ruby-operator">&gt;</span> <span class="ruby-keyword">end</span></pre>
                      </div>
                      <div class='source'>

                            <span style="color:#33B">@status</span> = <span style="background-color:hsla(0,100%,50%,0.05)"><span style="color:#710">'</span><span style="color:#D20">initialized</span><span style="color:#710">'</span></span>

                    <h2>Public Instance methods</h2>
                    <a name='method-i-execute'></a>
                    <section class='method public-instance' id='method-method-i-execute'>
                      <h3 class='synopsis'>
                        <span class='name'>execute</span>
                        <span class='arguments'>(function)</span>
                      </h3>
                      <div class='description'>

                        <p>Called by the child class&#39; execute function</p>
                        <ul><li>
                        <p><code>function</code> - The actual command that will be executed, passed in
                        from the sub class</p>
                        </li></ul>

                        <p>Examples</p>

                        <pre class="ruby">=<span class="ruby-operator">&gt;</span> <span class="ruby-comment">#inside child class, look at create_file.rb, copy_file.rb, or delete_file.rb for a complete example</span>&#x000A;=<span class="ruby-operator">&gt;</span> <span class="ruby-keyword">def</span> <span class="ruby-identifier">execute</span>&#x000A;=<span class="ruby-operator">&gt;</span>  <span class="ruby-identifier">function</span> = <span class="ruby-constant">Proc</span>.<span class="ruby-identifier">new</span> <span class="ruby-keyword">do</span> <span class="ruby-comment"># or Proc.new {}</span>&#x000A;=<span class="ruby-operator">&gt;</span>    <span class="ruby-comment">#code to be executed</span>&#x000A;=<span class="ruby-operator">&gt;</span>  <span class="ruby-keyword">end</span>&#x000A;=<span class="ruby-operator">&gt;</span>  <span class="ruby-keyword">super</span>(<span class="ruby-identifier">function</span>) <span class="ruby-comment"># (calls the super class&#39; execute function defined below)</span>&#x000A;=<span class="ruby-operator">&gt;</span> <span class="ruby-keyword">end</span></pre>
                      </div>
                      <div class='source'>
